ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend the class if someone is willing and able to put a lot of time into it.
Yes, especially to those who want to deepen knowledge about biophysical techniques.

I would say it was fairly difficult, but anyone who needs to use these techinques should take the class. Although I feel like I didnt gain as much as I could have from the class, for a lack of understanding, I did get exposure to these methods.
Yes, I would describe it as a spectroscopy course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I think the fundamentals behind the techiniques used to analyze metalloenzymes broadened my overall chemical understanding, applicable to both my discipline and research.
I learned a whole lot more about different types of spectroscopy, that was very useful.
